# Loading the dataset with https://www.kaggle.com/code/fkdplc/alzheimer-s-disease-stage-prediction


TRAIN_DIR = "/Users/zinebsordo/Desktop/classes/sta221/final_project/AlzheimerDataset/train/"
TEST_DIR = "/Users/zinebsordo/Desktop/classes/sta221/final_project/AlzheimerDataset/test/"
IMAGE_SIZE = 176
CLASSES = [
    'NonDemented',
    'VeryMildDemented',
    'MildDemented',
    'ModerateDemented',
]
train_images = {}
test_images = {}

for klass in CLASSES:
    train_images[klass] = []
    test_images[klass] = []

for klass in CLASSES:
    for image in os.listdir(TRAIN_DIR + klass):
        im = Image.open(TRAIN_DIR + klass + '/' + image).convert('L')
        train_images[klass].append(im.resize((IMAGE_SIZE, IMAGE_SIZE)))
        
    for image in os.listdir(TEST_DIR + klass):
        im = Image.open(TEST_DIR + klass + '/' + image).convert('L')
        test_images[klass].append(im.resize((IMAGE_SIZE, IMAGE_SIZE)))

# load train and test dataset
def load_dataset(xtrain, xtest, ytrain, ytest):
    # load dataset
    # reshape dataset to have a single channel
    xtrain = xtrain.reshape((xtrain.shape[0], 176, 176, 1))
    xtest = xtest.reshape((xtest.shape[0], 176, 176, 1))
    # one hot encode target values
    ytrain = to_categorical(ytrain)
    ytest = to_categorical(ytest)
    return xtrain, ytrain, xtest, ytest
 
# scale pixels
def prep_pixels(train, test):
    # convert from integers to floats
    train_norm = train.astype('float32')
    test_norm = test.astype('float32')
    # normalize to range 0-1
    train_norm = train_norm / 255.0
    test_norm = test_norm / 255.0
    # return normalized images
    return train_norm, test_norm
 
# define cnn model 1 
def define_model1(learning_rate):
   
    model = Sequential()

    # Convolutional layer 
    model.add(Conv2D(32, kernel_size=(3, 3), activation='relu', kernel_initializer='he_uniform', input_shape=(176, 176, 1)))
    model.add(MaxPooling2D((2, 2)))

    # Flattening layers of output of conv layer 
    model.add(Flatten())

    # Hidden Layer
    model.add(Dense(100, activation='relu', kernel_initializer='he_uniform'))

    # Output Layer
    model.add(Dense(4, activation='softmax'))

    # compile model
    # opt_sgd = SGD(learning_rate=0.01, momentum=0.9)
    opt_adam = Adam(learning_rate=learning_rate)

    
    model.compile(optimizer=opt_adam, loss=[tf.losses.CategoricalCrossentropy()], metrics=[tf.keras.metrics.AUC(name='auc')])
    return model


# define cnn model 2
def define_model2(learning_rate):

    model = Sequential()

    # First convolutional layers without dropout
    
    model.add(Conv2D(32, kernel_size=(3,3), padding='same', activation='relu', kernel_initializer='he_uniform', input_shape=(176, 176, 1)))
    model.add(MaxPooling2D(pool_size=(2,2)))
    model.add(BatchNormalization())
    
    model.add(Conv2D(64, kernel_size=(3,3), padding='same', activation='relu', kernel_initializer='he_uniform', input_shape=(176, 176, 1)))
    model.add(MaxPooling2D(pool_size=(2,2)))
    model.add(BatchNormalization())

    # Second convolutional layers with dropout

    model.add(Conv2D(128, kernel_size=(3,3), padding='same', activation='relu', kernel_initializer='he_uniform', input_shape=(176, 176, 1)))
    model.add(MaxPooling2D(pool_size=(2,2)))
    model.add(BatchNormalization())
    model.add(Dropout(0.2))

    model.add(Conv2D(256, kernel_size=(3,3), padding='same', activation='relu', kernel_initializer='he_uniform', input_shape=(176, 176, 1)))
    model.add(MaxPooling2D(pool_size=(2,2)))
    model.add(BatchNormalization())
    model.add(Dropout(0.2))

    # Flattening layers of output of conv layer 
    model.add(Flatten())

    # Hidden Layers
    model.add(Dense(512, activation='relu', kernel_initializer='he_uniform'))
    model.add(BatchNormalization())
    model.add(Dropout(0.5))
    
    model.add(Dense(128, activation='relu', kernel_initializer='he_uniform'))
    model.add(BatchNormalization())
    model.add(Dropout(0.2))

    model.add(Dense(64, activation='relu', kernel_initializer='he_uniform'))
    model.add(BatchNormalization())
    model.add(Dropout(0.1))


    # Output Layer
    model.add(Dense(4, activation='softmax'))

    # compile model
    opt_adam = Adam(learning_rate=learning_rate)
    model.compile(optimizer=opt_adam, loss=[tf.losses.CategoricalCrossentropy()], metrics=[tf.keras.metrics.AUC(name='auc')])

    return model

# evaluate a model using k-fold cross-validation
def evaluate_model_kfold(dataX, dataY, cv, batch_size, learning_rate, model):
    scores, histories = list(), list()
    # enumerate splits
    for train_ix, test_ix in cv.split(dataX):
        # define model
        if model=='model1':
            model = define_model1(learning_rate)
            # select rows for train and test
            trainX, trainY, testX, testY = dataX[train_ix], dataY[train_ix], dataX[test_ix], dataY[test_ix]
            # fit model
            history = model.fit(trainX, 
                                trainY, 
                                epochs=15, 
                                batch_size=batch_size,
                                validation_data=(testX, testY), 
                                callbacks = [EarlyStopping(monitor = 'val_auc', 
                                                           mode = 'max', 
                                                           patience=5, 
                                                           restore_best_weights=True)],
                                verbose=1)
            
            # evaluate model
            _, acc = model.evaluate(testX, testY, verbose=1)
            print('> %.3f' % (acc * 100.0))
            # stores scores
            scores.append(acc)
            histories.append(history)
        elif model=='model2':
            model = define_model2(learning_rate)
            # select rows for train and test
            trainX, trainY, testX, testY = dataX[train_ix], dataY[train_ix], dataX[test_ix], dataY[test_ix]
            # fit model
            history = model.fit(trainX, 
                                trainY,
                                epochs=50, 
                                batch_size=batch_size, 
                                validation_data=(testX, testY), 
                                verbose=1, 
                                callbacks = [EarlyStopping(monitor = 'val_auc', 
                                                           mode = 'max', 
                                                           patience=5, 
                                                           restore_best_weights=True)])
            # evaluate model
            _, acc = model.evaluate(testX, testY, verbose=1)
            print('> %.3f' % (acc * 100.0))
            # stores scores
            scores.append(acc)
            histories.append(history)
    return model, scores, histories

def evaluate_model(trainX, trainY, testX, testY, learning_rate, batch_size, model_type):
    scores, histories = list(), list()
    
    if model_type == 'model1':
        # define model
        model = define_model1(learning_rate)
        # fit model
        history = model.fit(trainX, 
                            trainY,
                            epochs=20, 
                            batch_size=batch_size,
                            verbose=1)
        # evaluate model
        _, auc = model.evaluate(testX, testY, verbose=1)
        print('> %.3f' % (auc))
        # stores scores
        scores.append(auc)
        histories.append(history)
        return model, scores, histories
    elif model_type == 'model2':
        
        # define model
        model = define_model2(learning_rate)
        # fit model
        history = model.fit(trainX, 
                            trainY,
                            epochs=20, 
                            batch_size=batch_size,
                            verbose=1)
        # evaluate model
        _, auc = model.evaluate(testX, testY, verbose=1)
        print('> %.3f' % (auc))
        # stores scores
        scores.append(auc)
        histories.append(history)
        return model, scores, histories
        
 
# run the test harness for evaluating a model
def run_test_harness():
    # load dataset
    trainX, trainY, testX, testY = load_dataset(xtrain, xtest, ytrain, yval)
    # prepare pixel data
    trainX, testX = prep_pixels(trainX, testX)
    # evaluate model
    scores, histories = evaluate_model_kfold(trainX, trainY)
    return scores, histories

# Load dataset and preproc
trainX, trainY, testX, testY = load_dataset(xtrain, xtest, ytrain, ytest)
# prepare pixel data
trainX, testX = prep_pixels(trainX, testX)

# Prepare gridsearch parameters to tune 
batch_size = [32, 64]
learning_rate = [0.01, 0.001, 0.0001]

# Run kfold evaluation on same kfolds cv and keep records of model, auc and fitted coefficients 
models_gs, params, scores_gs, histories_gs = [], [], [], []

n_folds=5
cv = KFold(n_folds, shuffle=True, random_state=1)
for x in tqdm(itertools.product(batch_size, learning_rate)):
    print("For batch_size = {} and learning_rate = {}".format(x[0], x[1]))
    model, scores, histories = evaluate_model_kfold(trainX, 
                                                    trainY, 
                                                    cv, 
                                                    batch_size=x[0], 
                                                    learning_rate=x[1],
                                                    model='model1')
    models_gs.append(model)
    params.append(x)
    scores_gs.append(scores)
    histories_gs.append(histories)

# plot diagnostic learning curves
def summarize_diagnostics(histories):
    
    fig, axes = plt.subplots(1, 2, figsize=(20,6))
    # plot of each kfold the list of auc obtained at each epoch
    axes[0].plot(histories[-1].history['auc'], color='blue', label='train AUC')
    axes[0].plot(histories[-1].history['val_auc'], color='orange', label='val AUC')
    axes[0].set_title('Classification AUC on last fold of CV on trainset', fontsize=17)
    axes[0].set_xlabel('Epoch', fontsize=15)
    axes[0].set_ylabel('Mean AUC per class prediction', fontsize=15)
    axes[0].legend()
    
    
    # plot of each kfold the list of loss obtained at each epoch
    axes[1].plot(histories[-1].history['loss'], color='blue', label='train cross-entropy loss')
    axes[1].plot(histories[-1].history['val_loss'], color='orange', label='val cross-entropy loss')
    axes[1].set_title('Loss', fontsize=17)
    axes[1].set_xlabel('Epoch', fontsize=15)
    axes[1].set_ylabel('Categorical crossentropy loss on last fold of CV on trainset', fontsize=15)
    axes[1].legend(fontsize=15)
    
    plt.show()
    
    
# summarize model performance
def summarize_performance(scores):
    # print summary
    print('AUC: mean=%.3f std=%.3f, n=%d' % (np.mean(scores)*100, np.std(scores)*100, len(scores)))
    # box and whisker plots of results
    plt.title('Distribution of the mean AUC (on predictions) for all k-folds')
    plt.tick_params(axis='x',          
                    which='both',      
                    bottom=False,      
                    top=False,         
                    labelbottom=False)
    plt.boxplot(scores)
    plt.show()

Adding gaussian noise for model diagnostics on best CNN model¶










In [36]:



     


# scale pixels for noisy data 
def prep_pixels_noisy(train, test, variance):
    
    # convert from integers to floats
    train_norm = train.astype('float32')
    test_norm = test.astype('float32')
    
    # Add noise to train set 
    train_noisy = train_norm.copy()
    m, v = 0, variance
    s = np.sqrt(v)
    for i in range(len(train_norm)):  
        gaussian = np.random.normal(m, s, (176, 176)) 
        train_noisy[i][:, :, 0] += gaussian
        
    # normalize to range 0-1
    train_norm = train_noisy / 255.0
    test_norm = test_norm / 255.0
    
    # return normalized noisy images
    return train_norm, test_norm

# Load data
trainX, trainY, testX, testY = load_dataset(xtrain, xtest, ytrain, ytest)

# Evaluate model for multiple values of noise variance
variances = [100, 10000, 5e6, 5e7, 5e10]
auc_vals = []
for v in tqdm(variances):
    trainX, testX = prep_pixels_noisy(trainX, testX, v)
    model, scores, histories = evaluate_model(trainX, trainY, testX, testY, 0.01, 32)
    auc_vals.append(scores)

def load_dataset_svm(xtrain, xval, ytrain, yval):
    # load dataset
    # reshape dataset to have a single channel
    xtrain = xtrain.reshape(xtrain.shape[0], -1)
    xval = xval.reshape(xval.shape[0], -1)
    # one hot encode target values
    ytrain = label_binarize(ytrain, classes = [0,1,2,3])
    yval = label_binarize(yval, classes = [0,1,2,3])
    return xtrain, ytrain, xval, yval
 
# scale pixels
def prep_pixels(train, test):
    # convert from integers to floats
    train_norm = train.astype('float32')
    test_norm = test.astype('float32')
    # normalize to range 0-1
    train_norm = train_norm / 255.0
    test_norm = test_norm / 255.0
    # return normalized images
    return train_norm, test_norm
